    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house in Toronto, is essentially a secure holding place for funds and documents until all the conditions of the sale are met. Think of it like a temporary, neutral holding spot, managed by a trusted third party—usually a lawyer or a real estate professional. It's crucial for the closing process because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money doesn't go to the seller until the title is officially transferred to you, and the house isn't handed over until the funds are secured. This process keeps everything from going sideways, which is vital when dealing with a large transaction like buying property.",
      "source": "target",
