    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A very important thing to watch out for is ensuring you are dealing with licensed and reputable professionals—your lawyer and realtor must be properly accredited. Scams can pop up as sudden demands for wire transfers to unfamiliar accounts, so always verify the bank details directly with your lawyer through a known, trusted channel. It's easy for a scammer to try and trick you into sending funds to a \"temporary\" account, which is a classic trick, so be wary of any urgency that feels too frantic. If you see anything that seems rushed or unusual, stop and call your lawyer directly to confirm.",
